==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Portage
<hw>Port"age</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From 2d
<er>Port</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A sailor's
wages when in port.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The amount of a sailor's
wages for a voyage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portage</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Portage
<hw>Port"age</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[3d <er>Port</er>.]</ety> <def>A
porthole.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portage</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Portage
<hw>Por"tage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., from
<ets>porter</ets> to carry. See <er>Port</er> to carry.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of carrying or transporting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The price of carriage; porterage.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Fell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Capacity for carrying; tonnage.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Hakluyt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A carry between navigable waters. See 3d
<er>Carry</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portage</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Portage
<hw>Por"tage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To carry
(goods, boats, etc.) overland between navigable waters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

